sql:
SELECT 
  c.Collection_Name, 
  c.Collection_ID, 
  COUNT(dic.Document_Object_ID) AS Number_of_Documents
FROM 
  Collections c
JOIN 
  Documents_in_Collections dic ON c.Collection_ID = dic.Collection_ID
GROUP BY 
  c.Collection_Name, c.Collection_ID
ORDER BY 
  Number_of_Documents DESC
LIMIT 1;
question: Which collection have most number of documents? List collection name, id and number of documents.
